monplace in an everyday business environment. The characters are fictitious, but the story comes from the author's own experience and real accounts. Each chapter ends with valuable lessons and conclusions drawn from events in the narrative, giving the reader a wealth of real-world, practical advice on what works, what fails, and the common traps and pitfalls to anticipate and avoid during an implementation project. People with little or no ITIL® experience, or even a limited IT background, will find this book interesting, entertaining and, above all, extremely useful in understanding the means to a successful implementation of a KPI management system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aInformation technologyxManagement. 0aInformation technologyxQuality control. 0aPerformance standards. 0aPerformance technology. 7aCOMPUTERS / General.2bisacsh  aIT service management.  aITIL.  aITSM.  aKPIs.  akey performance indicators.  ametrics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz978184928487540uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9781849284868  a978-3-11-150249-6  Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles